summary.snippet: "Clean, consistent, great service (staff & Management) and awesome ambience!"
"A waiter from across the dinning room was like “its over an hour wait on food."
"Great fried and roasted chicken with variety of flavors."

most_relevant.description: Let’s start with the positive. Clean and empty. That’s all I got for positives. The service was absolute garbage. What was even worse, was the excuse management attempted to give for their below lack luster type service. As pictured, establishment was barely 1/2 full but that was “busy”. 30mins to order food, 30mins to get us our bills as we watched management give his own family at a table 5 star service while our server elected to randomly clean tables as if we didn’t exist. The lack of prioritization was astonishing. After finally getting our food, orders were incorrect and food was lack luster. After seeing the behavior of management, I’m not even surprised at the servers inabilities. We remained kind and refrained from making a scene which would have been fully justified. Y’all looked like clowns!

Solid food and read fast! We ordered around 4pm and it was ready in under 15 minutes! Their wings are reliably and you know what you are getting. Best wings in the world? No. But solid if you like the flavorings offered. To be honest the reason that brought us back for a second time so soon is the fries! The are a really delicious shoestring with just the right about of crunch.

Waited 20 minutes to be seated, not because they was busy but because none of the workers wanted to seat anyone. A Waiter on his break sat me at a table with a menu. After waiting for 25 minutes and after three failed attempts to someone to take my order I decided to leave. A Waiter never came to my table and I don't want to be told they were short staffed because there were plenty of people walking around not working. I walked out and probably will never go back to this one.

I had a wonderful experience sitting at Erin's bar. She made excellent recommendations for drinks, and delivered our food promptly and accurately. As a 15+ year foodservice industry veteran, I feel confident attesting to Erin's skill and professionalism.

I have never posted a negative review for a restaurant, but tonight is the first time.  As someone who frequents multiple Buffalo Wild Wings, but also has worked in food service for 13+ years, my experience in this location was terrible. Service was bad and scarce and food quality was not good.

They got my order wrong. Several wings came with no sauce and another came with the sauce on the side, but I ordered sauces for all of them and none were supposed to be on the side. Plus, the sauce that came on the side wasn't even enough. I was charged normal price as well, and didn't get the chance to return because I noticed once they were already closed.
Waitress was awesome. Food was delicious

Great location for the South hotel district in Ann Arbor.  Always open late and a good time the night before GameDay.  It's BWW so food is consistent with other locations.  They also open early on game days with a 12pm start...good breaky.
